body:
This problem is just inherent to SDFs I think, because they are an approximation. They are very efficient and simple to use, but there's an equivalent price in visual fidelity.

You can try to improve things by either drawing the border and background together, or by dilation. The combined border and background approach requires a more complex, less efficent shader. Dilation tends to just move the visual artifacts elsewhere.

The combined border and background approach isn't sufficient to fix all the problems, unfortunately. I made a nice example, but then this morning forgot what it was and deleted it.. Hacked out some quick ones:

```rust
use bevy::prelude::*;

fn main() {
    App::new()
        .add_plugins(DefaultPlugins)
        .add_systems(Startup, setup)
        .run();
}

fn setup(mut commands: Commands) {
    commands.spawn(Camera2d);
    commands.insert_resource(ClearColor(Color::WHITE));
    commands.spawn((
        Node {
            justify_self: JustifySelf::Center,
            align_self: AlignSelf::Center,
            width: px(200),
            height: px(100),
            border: px(10).all(),
            ..default()
        },
        BorderRadius::MAX,
        BackgroundColor(Color::BLACK),
        BorderColor::all(Color::BLACK),
        Outline {
            width: px(5.),
            color: Color::BLACK,
            ..default()
        },
    ));
}
```

<img width="375" height="222" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/37fa045a-d549-4346-a6ae-aae8497ea90f" />

The example draws a solid black node with a black border, and a black outline, against a white background. You can see how pixels bleed through, not just at the node-border boundary, but also at the border-outline boundary. 

You could add outlines to the combined shader as well, but it's also possible to nest nodes:

```rust
use bevy::color::palettes::css::NAVY;
use bevy::prelude::*;

fn main() {
    App::new()
        .add_plugins(DefaultPlugins)
        .add_systems(Startup, setup)
        .run();
}

fn setup(mut commands: Commands) {
    commands.spawn(Camera2d);
    commands.spawn((
        Node {
            justify_self: JustifySelf::Center,
            align_self: AlignSelf::Center,
            width: px(200),
            height: px(200),
            border: px(20).all(),
            ..default()
        },
        BorderColor::all(Color::BLACK),
        BackgroundColor(Color::WHITE),
        BorderRadius::MAX,
        children![(
            Node {
                justify_self: JustifySelf::Center,
                align_self: AlignSelf::Center,
                width: px(160),
                height: px(160),
                ..default()
            },
            BorderRadius::MAX,
            BackgroundColor(NAVY.into()),
        )],
    ));
}
```

